  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency sanitation, hygiene and protection assistance to Congolese refugees</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this project is to improve emergency sanitation, hygiene and protection assistance to affected Congolese refugees and vulnerable communities by: 1) ensuring Uganda&#x2019;s immigration and government officials are able to rapidly respond to a sudden influx in refugees from DRC and abide by international protection guidelines and protocols, as well as 2) reduce the risks of propagation of WASH related diseases among the refugee population and host communities through improved access to sanitary facilities and improved hygiene and sanitation practices at Sebagoro landing site and Kyangwali settlement.</narrative>
  </description>
